<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-2470] THttpHandler swallows exceptions from processor</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2470</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The THttpHandler.ProcessRequest() method currently swallows any exceptions by the processor, and writes them out to Console.Error. This makes it very difficult to figure out what&apos;s going on if an exception is thrown in anything other than a console application.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12708770">THRIFT-2470</key>
