                            <comment id="13972391" author="githubbot" created="Thu, 17 Apr 2014 08:21:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Github user adam-resdiary commented on the pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/100#issuecomment-40691732&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/100#issuecomment-40691732&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    I only ran the tests in VS, but I can certainly try them out in MonoDevelop on my mac when I get a chance. I figured that since NUnit and Moq are pretty standard for unit testing in the .NET world, and that the test project wouldn&apos;t be distributed with the library (and therefore those dependencies won&apos;t be distributed either) it would be ok. Does that reasoning make sense?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Cheers for committing the fix though.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
